line of emergency remote education, Voices from the Digital Classroom portrays the struggles, innovations, and resilience of students, instructors, and educational professionals in the face of COVID-19. These interviews offer a unique, of-the-moment perspective on an exceptional time. Complemented by additional voices that expand on stories told to reflect on challenges, successes, and lessons learned, Voices from the Digital Classroom is both a time-capsule and a vision for the future. It provides new insights into pandemic teaching and learning, a remarkable lens into the daily realities of the digital classroom, and an inspiration for the future of remote education in a post-pandemic world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aEDUCATION / Virtual & Hybrid.2bisacsh  aCOVID learning.  aCOVID teaching.  aCOVID-19.  aRemote learning.  ahigher education.  ainterviews.  aonline classes.  aonline learning.  apandemic classroom.  apandemic learning.  apandemic teaching.  apedagogy.  apivot to online.  apivot to remote.  aremote education.  astudents.  ateachers.  avirtual learning.1 aAbegglen, Sandra, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMotta, Frances, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeuhaus, Fabian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aParker, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalinas, Julian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpiers, Alex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilson, Kylie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Up